headline: Tidal Cyber Appoints Jessica Hall as Vice President of Product
summary: Tidal Cyber, the creator of the Threat-Led Defense category, today announced the appointment of Jessica Hall as Vice President of Product. Hall will lead product development and execution as the company accelerates platform innovation to help organizations operationalize MITRE ATT&CK and map defenses to adversary behavior, reduce residual risk, and align security investments to real-world threats.

headline: Is CoStar (CSGP) Using Its New $1.5 Billion Buyback To Redefine Its Growth Story?
summary: In early January 2026, CoStar Group announced 2026 guidance calling for US$3.78 billion to US$3.82 billion in revenue and US$0.42 to US$0.52 in diluted EPS, alongside net income of US$175 million to US$215 million. The company also completed a US$500 million repurchase plan and approved a new US$1.50 billion buyback program, highlighting a sharper focus on capital returns and Homes.com investment efficiency.
